item.title: Gold Steady as Fed Meeting Awaited
item.description: Gold prices were steady as investors awaited the conclusion of the Fed’s meeting Wednesday, which will be scrutinized for any forward-looking clues.

item.title: EUR/USD's Bias Remains Bearish Below 1.0770, Charts Show
item.description: EUR/USD’s bias remains bearish below a recent high of 1.0770, based on technical charts, and although the pair found support around the May low and has rebounded over the past two sessions, it is still within a clear downtrend on the daily chart.

item.title: Brent Briefly Rises Above $95 Following Saudi Energy Minister Comments
item.description: Oil prices briefly rose above $95 a barrel after Saudi Arabia’s energy minister said the “jury is still out” on demand from China, interpreted as an indication the kingdom anticipates leaving its supply cut in place into next year, ANZ said.

item.title: Kingfisher Cuts Full-Year Guidance
item.description: Kingfisher now sees its adjusted pretax profit for fiscal 2024 at £590 million, after first-half profits missed consensus, driven largely by a weaker sales performance in Poland.

item.title: How Russia Is Building Up Its Arsenal of Low-Cost Explosive Drones
item.description: Early in its invasion of Ukraine, Russia lagged behind Kyiv in its use of low-cost explosive drones. But by mid 2023, Russian UAVs were targeting Ukrainian forces, copying some of Kyiv’s most successful tactics. WSJ explains how Moscow is catching up.

item.title: Australia Declares El Niño Underway, Warns of Reduced Rainfall
item.description: Australia said an El Niño weather pattern is under way, bringing with it a heightened risk of wildfires, heat waves and reduced rainfall to one of the world’s largest exporters of agricultural products.

item.title: Kingfisher's Comments on Regional Performance Will Be Keenly Watched
item.description: Kingfisher could see consensus estimates lowered 5%-6% on the back of its guidance cut, Citi said, keeping a neutral rating on the stock and a 256p price target.

item.title: Ocado Keeps Outlook As Sales Rise
item.description: Ocado left its full-year guidance unchanged on positive momentum heading into the final quarter after it reported a 7.2% rise in third-quarter revenue.

item.title: Finnish Auction Bonds Seen Offering Limited Relative Value
